CatDescriptText: Garfield Dawkins, musician, 2139 Rose Street, was part of the Pittsburgher's Speak Up column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 5, 1959, with question: "Do you believe Allegheny County Democrats and Republicans have selected their best candidates for public offices in past 10 years?"  Answer reads: "I think so. Each party selects its best candidates for respective jobs."
